data.content:
**Yes, C# fully supports `stackalloc`'d `Span` of native-sized integers.** Both `nint` and `nuint` work:

```csharp
Span<nint> span = stackalloc nint[4];
Span<nuint> uspan = stackalloc nuint[3];
```

Tested on .NET 10.0 — compiles and runs without issues. This has been supported since C# 9 / .NET 5, when `nint`/`nuint` were introduced as first-class unmanaged types (they satisfy the `unmanaged` constraint required by `stackalloc`).
